. a. sierrae''\n| ''M. a. vancouverensis''\n| ''M. a. vulpina''\n}}\n|range=Northern North America |range-image=File:American Marten area.png |range-image-size=180px\n|size={{convert|46|\u2013|66|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} long, plus {{convert|13|\u2013|16|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} tail<ref name=\"Americanmartensize\"/>\n|habitat=Forest<ref name=\"IUCNAmericanmarten\"/>\n|hunting=Primarily eats rodents and small mammals, as well as birds, insects, fruit, and carrion<ref name=\"IUCNAmericanmarten\"/>\n|iucn-status=LC |population=Unknown\n|direction={{decrease|Population declining}}<ref name=\"IUCNAmericanmarten\"/>\n}}\n{{Species table/row\n|name=[[Beech marten]] |binomial=M. foina\n|image=File:Steinmarder (cropped).jpg |image-size=114px |image-alt=Brown and white mustelid indoors\n|authority-name=[[Johann Christian Polycarp Erxleben|Erxleben]] |authority-year=1777\n|subspecies={{Collapsible list |expand= |title=Eleven subspecies |bullets=on\n| ''M. f. bosniaca'' (Balkan beech marten)\n| ''M. f. bunites'' (Cretan beech marten)\n| ''M. f. foina'' (European beech marten)\n| ''M. f. intermedia'' (Middle Asian beech marten)\n| ''M. f. kozlovi'' (Tibetan beech marten)\n| ''M. f. mediterranea'' (Iberian beech marten)\n| ''M. f. milleri'' (Rhodes beech marten)\n| ''M. f. nehringi'' (Caucasian beech marten)\n| ''M. f. rosanowi'' (Crimean beech marten)\n| ''M. f. syriaca'' (Syrian beech marten)\n| ''M. f. toufoeus'' (Lhasa beech marten)\n}}\n|range=Europe and central Asia |range-image=File:Beech Marten area.png |range-image-size=180px\n|size={{convert|40|\u2013|50|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} long, plus {{convert|22|\u2013|30|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} tail<ref name=\"ADWBeechmarten\"/>\n|habitat=Forest, rocky areas, and shrubland<ref name=\"IUCNBeechmarten\"/>\n|hunting=Primarily eats rodents and small mammals, as well as birds, insects, fruit, and carrion<ref name=\"IUCNBeechmarten\"/>\n|iucn-status=LC |population=Unknown\n|direction={{steady|Population steady}}<ref name=\"IUCNBeechmarten\"/>\n}}\n{{Species ta