on clawless otter]])\n| ''A. c. hindei''\n| ''A. c. meneleki''\n| ''A. c. microdon''\n| ''A. c. philippsi''\n}}\n|range=Sub-Saharan Africa |range-image=File:African Clawless Otter area.png |range-image-size=165px\n|size={{convert|72|\u2013|95|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} long, plus {{convert|40|\u2013|60|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} tail<ref name=\"OSGAfricanclawlessotter\"/>\n|habitat=Forest, inland wetlands, [[neritic zone|neritic marine]], coastal marine, [[intertidal zone|intertidal marine]], and grassland<ref name=\"IUCNAfricanclawlessotter\"/>\n|hunting=Primarily eats crabs and lobsters, as well as frogs, fish, and insects<ref name=\"OSGAfricanclawlessotter\"/><ref name=\"IUCNAfricanclawlessotter\"/>\n|iucn-status=NT |population=Unknown\n|direction={{decrease|Population declining}}<ref name=\"IUCNAfricanclawlessotter\"/>\n}}\n{{Species table/row\n|name=[[Asian small-clawed otter]] |binomial=A. cinerea<!--MSW3 has this in Aonyx, though WP has it in Amblonyx-->\n|image=File:Otter - melbourne zoo.jpg |image-size=180px |image-alt=Brown mustelid on a mossy rock\n|authority-name=[[Johann Karl Wilhelm Illiger|Illiger]] |authority-year=1815\n|subspecies={{Collapsible list |expand=yes |title=Three subspecies |bullets=on\n| ''A. c. cinerea''\n| ''A. c. concolor''\n| ''A. c. nirnai''\n}}\n|range=Southeast Asia |range-image=File:Oriental Small-clawed Otter area.png |range-image-size=172px\n|size={{convert|40|\u2013|63|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} long, plus {{convert|25|\u2013|35|cm|in|0|abbr=on}} tail<ref name=\"OSGAsiansmall-clawedotter\"/>\n|habitat=Intertidal marine, coastal marine, inland wetlands, forest, shrubland, neritic marine, and grassland<ref name=\"IUCNAsiansmall-clawedotter\"/>\n|hunting=Primarily eats crabs, molluscs, insects, and small fish, as well as rodents, snakes, and amphibians<ref name=\"IUCNAsiansmall-clawedotter\"/>\n|iucn-status=VU |population=Unknown\n|direction={{decrease|Population declining}}<ref name=\"IUCNAsiansmall-clawedotter\"/>\n}}\n{{Species table/end}}\n{{Species ta