{"title_page": "List of dictionaries by number of words", "text_new": "{{Expand list|date=August 2016}}\n\nThis is a list of dictionaries considered authoritative or complete by approximate number of total [[word]]s, or [[headword]]s, included.  These figures do not take account of entries with senses for different word classes (such as noun and adjective) and [[homograph]]s. Although it is possible to count the number of entries in a dictionary, it is not possible to count the number of words in a language.<ref>{{cite web|title=How many words are there in the English language?|url=http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/words/how-many-words-are-there-in-the-english-language|publisher=[[Oxford English Dictionary]]|accessdate=14 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Biggest Vocabulary?|url=https://www.economist.com/johnson/2010/06/23/the-biggest-vocabulary|publisher=[[The Economist]]|date=23 June 2010|accessdate=14 August 2018}}</ref> In compiling a dictionary, a lexicographer decides whether the evidence of use is sufficient to justify an entry in the dictionary. This decision is not the same as determining whether the word exists.{{citation needed|date=October 2016}}\n\nThe green background means a given dictionary is the largest in a given language.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Language\n! colspan=2 | Approx. no. of words\n! Dictionary\n! Notes\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Korean language|Korean]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 1,100,373 ||0.0001}}\n|\uc6b0\ub9ac\ub9d0\uc0d8 (Woori Mal Saem, 2017)\n|Online open dictionary including dialects of South and North Korea.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://opendict.korean.go.kr/service/dicStat|title=\"\uc6b0\ub9ac\ub9d0\uc0d8 - \uc0ac\uc804 \ud1b5\uacc4\"|last=|first=|date=|website=\uc6b0\ub9ac\ub9d0\uc0d8|access-date=2017-11-09}}{{dead link|date=November 2018|bot=medic}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Finnish language|Finnish]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 800,000 ||0.0001}}\n|RedFox Pro\n|Online dictionary. The free version has over 300,000 Finnish words and the Pro version has over 800,000 Finnish words. The dictionary has agglomerated other dictionaries, such as technical ones<ref>{{cite web|url=https://redfoxsanakirja.fi/sisaltopaivitykset | title=RedFox Sanakirja: Sis\u00e4lt\u00f6p\u00e4ivitykset. | publisher=Redfox languages Oy | accessdate=2019-08-08 | language=Finnish}}</ref>, and the largest set comes from [[Wordnet]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yle.fi/uutiset/3-7627675 | title=Suomen suurin sanakirja julkaistiin ilmaisena netiss\u00e4 | publisher=[[Yle]] | accessdate=2019-08-08 | language=Finnish}}</ref>. Note that even this dictionary essentially doesn't include inflections.\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Turkish language|Turkish]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 616,767 ||0.0001}}\n|B\u00fcy\u00fck T\u00fcrk\u00e7e S\u00f6zl\u00fck\n|Online dictionary of the [[Turkish Language Association]]<ref>{{cite web|title=B\u00fcy\u00fck T\u00fcrk\u00e7e S\u00f6zl\u00fck|url=http://www.tdk.gov.tr/index.php?option=com_bts|publisher=[[Turkish Language Association]]|accessdate=27 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Swedish language|Swedish]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 600,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Svenska Akademiens ordbok]], [[Swedish Academy]]\n|After having completed letters '''''A''''' through '''''T''''' SAOB included 470,000 words, but 600,000 words when the alphabet was completed in 2017. [[Svenska Akademiens ordlista]], which includes only commonly used words, currently includes ~126,000 words after having added 13,500 and removed 9,000 in its latest edition, SAOL 14, plus an additional 200,000 still encountered words in earlier editions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://videnskab.dk/kultur-samfund/engelsk-har-naeppe-flere-ord-end-dansk|title=Engelsk har n\u00e6ppe flere ord end dansk|website=videnskab.dk|access-date=2016-08-14}}</ref><ref>[http://www.svenskaakademien.se/svenska-spraket/svenska-akademiens-ordlista-saol SAOL]. Svenska Akademien. Retrieved 14 August 2016.</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Icelandic language|Icelandic]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 560,000 ||0.0001}}\n|Or\u00f0ab\u00f3k H\u00e1sk\u00f3lans\n| 43,000 basic words and 519,000 [[compound word]]s of which more than half are attested only once or don't get into print (\u201cinstant combinations\u201d)<ref>{{cite web|title=Hva\u00f0 eru til m\u00f6rg or\u00f0 \u00ed \u00edslensku?|url=http://www.visindavefur.is/svar.php?id=738|publisher=[[University of Iceland]]|accessdate=7 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Italian language|Italian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 500,000 ||0.0001}}\n|Grande Dizionario Hoepli Italiano<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hoepli.it/libro/grande-dizionario-hoepli-italiano/9788820366957.html|title=Grande dizionario Hoepli italiano|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://dizionari.repubblica.it/italiano.html|title=Dizionario di italiano|accessdate=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n|The number of \"sayable and writable\" word-forms is estimated at over 2 million<ref>{{cite web|title=Quante parole ci sono nel dizionario italiano?|url=http://www.treccani.it/lingua_italiana/domande_e_risposte/varie/varie_026.html|accessdate=23 February 2017}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Japanese language|Japanese]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 500,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Nihon Kokugo Daijiten]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=NIHON KOKUGO DAIJITEN|url=https://libraries.indiana.edu/nihon-kokugo-daijiten|publisher=[[Indiana University]]|accessdate=7 August 2016}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Lithuanian language|Lithuanian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 500,000 ||0.0001}}\n|Lietuvi\u0173 kalbos \u017eodynas (Academic Dictionary of Lithuanian)\n|22,000 pages in 20 volumes with quotations from all kinds of writing and dialect records between 1547 and 2001. Accessible online at [http://www.lkz.lt/ www.lkz.lt].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lkz.lt/en/dze.htm|title=Dictionary of the Lithuanian Language|date=2002|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811103658/http://www.lkz.lt/en/dze.htm|archive-date=2017-08-11|url-status=live|access-date=April 19, 2018}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[English language|English]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 505,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Wiktionary|Wiktionary, english language version]]\n|Contains 505,000 gloss entries<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Special:Statistics|title=Statistics |website=en.wiktionary.org|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[English language|English]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 470,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Webster's Third New International Dictionary]] and Addenda Section\n|Contains 470,000 entries<ref name=Webster>{{Cite web|url=https://www.merriam-webster.com/help/faq-how-many-english-words|title=How many words are there in English? |website=www.merriam-webster.com|access-date=2018-05-15}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 442,000 ||0.0001}}\n|Novo Dicionario Houaiss da Lingua Portuguesa\n|The dictionary contains 442,000 entries, phrases and meanings.{{cn|date=November 2019}}\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Dutch language|Dutch]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 400,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Woordenboek der Nederlandsche Taal]]\n|The 43 volumes of the WNT (including three supplements) consist of 49,255 pages, describing Dutch words from 1500 to 1976.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://ivdnt.org/onderzoek-a-onderwijs/lexicologie-a-lexicografie/wnt | title=Woordenboek der Nederlandsche Taal |access-date=9 August 2017}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Chinese language|Chinese]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 370,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Hanyu Da Cidian]]\n|<ref>[https://baike.baidu.com/item/%E6%B1%89%E8%AF%AD%E5%A4%A7%E8%AF%8D%E5%85%B8 \u6c49\u8bed\u5927\u8bcd\u5178_\u767e\u5ea6\u767e\u79d1]. Retrieved 17 June 2019.</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[English language|English]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 350,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[The American Heritage Dictionary of the English Language]], Third Edition\n|In the introduction to the 4th and 5th editions, it is mentioned that more than 10,000 words have been added, thus the total for the 5th edition will be more than 370,000 words.<ref>https://www.amazon.com/American-Heritage-Dictionary-English-Language/dp/0395448956</ref>{{failedverification|date=May 2019}}\n\n|-\n|[[Finnish language|Finnish]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 350,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Suomen murteiden sanakirja]] (in progress)\n|Suomen murteiden sanakirja (SMS) will include 350,000 words from different dialects, with well-documented definitions, based on the archives (Suomen murteiden sana-arkisto) of 400,000 words, with over 8 million definitions.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kaino.kotus.fi/sms/ | title=Suomen murteiden sanakirja | publisher=[[Institute for the Languages of Finland]] | accessdate=2019-08-08|language=Finnish}}</ref> <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kotus.fi/aineistot/sana-aineistot/suomen_murteiden_sana-arkisto/paakokoelma | title=\tSuomen murteiden sana-arkisto: P\u00e4\u00e4kokoelma | publisher=[[Institute for the Languages of Finland]] | accessdate=2019-08-08|language=Finnish}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Persian language|Persian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 343,466  ||0.0001}}\n|Dehkhoda Dictionary, 1998, {{ISBN|9789640396025}}\n|The original series initially consisted of 3 million records (\u0641\u06cc\u0634 fish or \u0628\u0631\u06af\u0647 bargeh in Persian) (up to 100 records for each word or proper noun) until Dehkhoda's death in November 1955, and currently contains 343,466 entries that according to the latest digital release of the dictionary by Tehran University Press (version 3.0) are based on an ever-growing library of over 2300 volumes in lexicology and various other scientific fields.<ref> https://icps.ut.ac.ir/talif-f.html</ref> <ref> https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dehkhoda_Dictionary</ref>\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Norwegian language|Norwegian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 330,000 ||0.0001}}\n|Norsk Ordbok\n|The finished dictionary has about 330,000 headwords, whersas the corpus it's built upon, conatains about 500,000 words in total.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sprakradet.no/svardatabase/sporsmal-og-svar/antall-ord-i-norsk/|title=Antall ord i norsk|website=Spr\u00e5kr\u00e5det|language=no|access-date=2017-09-29}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[German language|German]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 330,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Deutsches W\u00f6rterbuch]]\n|330,000 words in use since the mid-fifteenth century. \u2014 [[Duden]]'s ''Gro\u00dfes W\u00f6rterbuch der deutschen Sprache'' contains over 200,000 contemporary words.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gro\u00dfes W\u00f6rterbuch der deutschen Sprache|url=http://www.woerterbuch-portal.de/woebus_alle/Woebu23?krit=|publisher=[[Berlin-Brandenburg Academy of Sciences and Humanities]]|accessdate=16 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Deutsches W\u00f6rterbuch von Jacob Grimm und Wilhelm Grimm (The German Dictionary of the Brothers Grimm)|url=http://www.bbaw.de/en/research/dwb|publisher=[[Berlin-Brandenburg Academy of Sciences and Humanities]] & [[Heidelberg Academy of Sciences and Humanities]]|accessdate=16 August 2016}} Also [http://woerterbuchnetz.de/DWB/ available online].</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[Norwegian language|Norwegian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 300,000 ||0.0001}}\n|Tanums store rettskrivningsordbok (10. utgave)\n|<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sprakradet.no/svardatabase/sporsmal-og-svar/antall-ord-i-norsk/|title=Antall ord i norsk|website=Spr\u00e5kr\u00e5det|language=no|access-date=2017-09-29}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Gujarati language|Gujarati]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 281,377 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Bhagavadgomandal]]\n|2.81 [[lakh]] words and their meanings in 9 volumes. Also serves as an encyclopedia with almost 8.22 lakh words.<ref>{{Cite web|title=What is Bhagavadgomanal?|url=http://www.bhagavadgomandalonline.com/bhagavadgomandal.html|website=bhagavadgomandalonline.com|publisher=Pravin Prakashan Pvt. Ltd.|access-date=2018-03-04}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Urdu language|Urdu]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 264000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Urdu Lughat]]\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=New Urdu dictionary heavily influenced by TV news|url=https://tribune.com.pk/story/2018901/1-new-urdu-dictionary-heavily-influenced-tv-news|publisher=[[tribune]]|accessdate=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Czech language|Czech]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 250,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[:cs:P\u0159\u00edru\u010dn\u00ed slovn\u00edk jazyka \u010desk\u00e9ho]]\n|Nine volumes of this dictionary were printed in years 1935-1957. They contain about 250,000 words, their meanings and example usage from literature. The dictionary is [http://bara.ujc.cas.cz/psjc/ available online].<ref>{{Cite web|title=P\u0159\u00edru\u010dn\u00ed slovn\u00edk jazyka \u010desk\u00e9ho|url=http://www.ujc.cas.cz/elektronicke-slovniky-a-zdroje/Prirucni_slovik_jazyka_ceskeho.html|website=www.ujc.cas.cz}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Belarusian language|Belarusian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 223,000 ||0.0001}}\n|\u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u043e\u0439 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044c \u0431\u0435\u043b\u043e\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u044f\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430\n|<ref>[https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=73389&lang=ru]</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[English language|English]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 207,016 ||0.0001}}\n|[[WordNet]], 3.1\n|{{as of|2012|November}} WordNet's latest Online-version is 3.1. The database contains 155,327 words organized in 175,979 synsets for a total of 207,016 word-sense pairs.<ref>https://wordnet.princeton.edu</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[Finnish language|Finnish]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 201,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Nykysuomen sanakirja]], 1961\n|Nykysuomen sanakirja can be translated to The Dictionary of Modern Finnish or The Dictionary of Contemporary Finnish, but the language can be quite dated; the dictionary only reflects the language as it was no later than 1961. Even though it has been published again, it has not been updated. The dictionary contains over 201,000 headwords in six volumes.<ref>Kolehmainen, Taru: {{Cite web|url=https://www.kielikello.fi/-/viisikymmenta-vuotta-nykysuomen-sanakirjan-alullepanosta | title=Viisikymment\u00e4 vuotta Nykysuomen sanakirjan alullepanosta. | publisher=[[Institute for the Languages of Finland]] | accessdate=2019-08-08|language=Finnish}} Kielikello 10/1977.</ref> For modern language, [[The New Dictionary of Modern Finnish]] is more relevant.\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Danish language|Danish]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 200,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Ordbog over det danske Sprog]]\n|Dictionary maintained by the [[Society for Danish Language and Literature]]. Covers Dansh language use 1700-1950.<ref>[https://ordnet.dk/ods Ordbog over det danske Sprog], [[Society for Danish Language and Literature]]</ref> The society also maintains a sister dictionary, ''[[Den Danske Ordbog]]'' covering language use since 1950.\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Slovak language|Slovak]]\n|align=right| {{bartable| 200,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[http://www.juls.savba.sk/ssj_peciar.html Slovn\u00edk slovensk\u00e9ho jazyka] z r. 1959 \u2013 1968, [http://www.juls.savba.sk/pub_sssj.html Slovn\u00edk s\u00fa\u010dasn\u00e9ho slovensk\u00e9ho jazyka A \u2013 G, H \u2013 L, M \u2013 N] z r. 2006, 2011, 2015\n|Here is the information about the number of words in Slovak language written by [http://www.juls.savba.sk/ Jazykovedn\u00fd \u00fastav <abbr>\u013d.</abbr> \u0160t\u00fara] <abbr>SAV.</abbr>\n\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Romanian language|Romanian]]\n|align=right| {{bartable| 180,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[https://dexonline.ro/ dexonline]\n|Online dictionary. Project of digitisation of 67 general, specialty and archaic dictionaries. Launched in 2001. As of 2013, it contained over [[Dic\u021bionarul explicativ al limbii rom\u00e2ne|180,000 unique words]] and 576,000 definitions.\n\n|-\n|[[English language|English]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 171,476 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Oxford English Dictionary]], Second Edition\n|Oxford Dictionary has 273,000 [[headword]]s; 171,476 of them being in current use, 47,156 being [[obsolete word]]s and around 9,500 derivative words included as subentries. The dictionary contains 157,000 combinations and derivatives in [[bold]] type, and 169,000 phrases and combinations in bold [[italic type]], making a total of over 600,000 word-forms.<ref>Robert McCrum, William Cran, & Robert MacNeil. The Story of English. New York: Penguin, 1992: 1</ref><ref>Oxford English Dictionary, Second Edition, Volume 1. Oxford University Press, 1989.</ref><br>There is one count that puts the English vocabulary at about 1 million words \u2014 but that count presumably includes words such as Latin [[species name]]s, [[prefix]]ed and [[suffix]]ed words, [[scientific terminology]], [[jargon]], foreign words of extremely limited English use and technical [[acronym]]s.{{sfn|Algeo|1999}}<ref>{{cite web|title=How many words are there in the English language?|url=http://www.oxforddictionaries.com/words/how-many-words-are-there-in-the-english-language|publisher=[[Oxford English Dictionary]]|accessdate=6 August 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"AartsChalker2014\">{{cite book|author1=Bas Aarts|author2=Sylvia Chalker|author3=Edmund Weiner|title=The Oxford Dictionary of English Grammar|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=9zVOCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA436|date=16 January 2014|publisher=OUP Oxford|isbn=978-0-19-107900-9|pages=436\u2013}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[Kazakh language|Kazakh]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 166,000 ||0.0001}}\n|15 \u0442\u043e\u043c\u0434\u044b\u049b \"\u049a\u0430\u0437\u0430\u049b \u0442\u0456\u043b\u0456\u043d\u0456\u04a3 \u0442\u04af\u0441\u0456\u043d\u0434\u0456\u0440\u043c\u0435 \u0441\u04e9\u0437\u0434\u0456\u0433\u0456\"  \n|Explanatory dictionary of the Kazakh language<ref>https://www.inform.kz/kz/15-tomdyk-kazak-adebi-tili-sozdiginin-tusaukeseri-otedi_a2428253</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Russian language|Russian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 150,000 ||0.0001}}\n|\u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u043e\u0439 \u0430\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044c \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u044f\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430 \n|Great Academy Dictionary of Russian language<ref>[https://dic.academic.ru/book.nsf/64290842/\u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u043e\u0439%20\u0430\u043a\u0430\u0434\u0435\u043c\u0438\u0447\u0435\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439%20\u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044c%20\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e%20\u044f\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430]</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[Belarusian language|Belarusian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 150,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[:be:\u0421\u043b\u043e\u045e\u043d\u0456\u043a \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0439 \u043c\u043e\u0432\u044b|\u0421\u043b\u043e\u045e\u043d\u0456\u043a \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0430\u0439 \u043c\u043e\u0432\u044b]]\n|<ref>[http://belnauka.by/component/mtree/realizovannye/slo-nik-belaruskaj-movy.html]</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[French language|French]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 135,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Tr\u00e9sor de la langue fran\u00e7aise|Tr\u00e9sor de la Langue Fran\u00e7aise informatis\u00e9]]\n|ATILF<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.atilf.fr/spip.php?rubrique66|title=Presentation - Site du laboratoire ATILF|last=|first=|date=|website=www.atilf.fr|publisher=|language=English|access-date=2016-10-28}}</ref> (''Analyse et Traitement Informatique de la Langue Fran\u00e7aise'' \u2013 Computer Processing and Analysis of the French Language)<br>135,000 (''Larousse Dictionnaire de fran\u00e7ais'', published by [[Editions Larousse]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.larousse.com/en/dictionaries/french|title=French Dictionary|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=[[\u00c9ditions Larousse|Larousse]]|language=English|accessdate=28 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.atilf.fr/spip.php?rubrique77|title=TLFi : Tr\u00e9sor de la Langue Fran\u00e7aise informatis\u00e9 - Site du laboratoire ATILF|last=|first=|date=|website=www.atilf.fr|publisher=|language=French|access-date=2016-10-28}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Ukrainian language|Ukrainian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 134,058 ||0.0001}}\n|\u0421\u043b\u043e\u0432\u043d\u0438\u043a \u0443\u043a\u0440\u0430\u0457\u043d\u0441\u044c\u043a\u043e\u0457 \u043c\u043e\u0432\u0438 (The Dictionary of the Ukrainian language)\n|The dictionary was finished in late 1970s - early 1980s<ref>[http://www.inmo.org.ua/sum.html]</ref><ref>[http://sum.in.ua/]</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[Russian language|Russian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 130,000 ||0.0001}}\n|\u0411\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0448\u043e\u0439 \u0442\u043e\u043b\u043a\u043e\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u043b\u043e\u0432\u0430\u0440\u044c \u0440\u0443\u0441\u0441\u043a\u043e\u0433\u043e \u044f\u0437\u044b\u043a\u0430 \n|Great Dictionary of Russian language<ref>[https://gufo.me/dict/kuznetsov]</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Indonesian language|Indonesian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 127,036 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Great Dictionary of the Indonesian Language of the Language Center|Kamus Besar Bahasa Indonesia]], 5th edition, 2016\n|\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 124,405 ||0.0001}}\n|[[University of Madras]] [[Tamil Lexicon dictionary|Tamil Lexicon]]\n|The dictionary includes 124,405 separate entries.<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/2005/04/29/stories/2005042915320300.htm]. TheHindu.com. Retrieved 11 July 2017.</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Arabic language|Arabic]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 120,000 ||0.0001}}\n|Taj al-Arus Min Jawahir al-Qamus\n|\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Bulgarian language|Bulgarian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 119,200 ||0.0001}}\n|[http://ibl.bas.bg/rbe/ Dictionary of the Bulgarian Language] (monolingual academic explanatory dictionary), ''(\u041c\u043d\u043e\u0433\u043e\u0442\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d) \u0420\u0435\u0447\u043d\u0438\u043a \u043d\u0430 \u0431\u044a\u043b\u0433\u0430\u0440\u0441\u043a\u0438\u044f \u0435\u0437\u0438\u043a'' in Bulgarian, in 15+ volumes\n|This dictionary covers vocabulary from the last 150 years of the Bulgarian language and is compiled and edited by linguistics (primarily native lexicographers and lexicologists) from The Institute for the Bulgarian Language (part of the [[Bulgarian Academy of Sciences]]). It includes basic, commonly used, literary, colloquial, dialectical, archaic and obsolete Bulgarian words, as well as some specialized terminology. The latest volume (15th) published in 2015 ends with [[headword]]s beginning with the (Bulgarian Cyrillic) letter '''''[[Er (Cyrillic)|\u0420]]'''''.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://ibl.bas.bg/rbe/ | title=Online edition of the 15 volumes of The (Explanatory) Dictionary of the Bulgarian Language (in Bulgarian) | publisher=many publishers, primarily The Academic Publishing House of The Institute for the Bulgarian Language | accessdate=October 29, 2016}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[Belarusian language|Belarusian]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 112,462 ||0.0001}}\n|Skarnik \n|{{as of|2019|August}}. Belarusian-Russian online dictionary contains 112,462 words.<ref>https://www.skarnik.by/belrus</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Slovenian language|Slovene]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 110,180 ||0.0001}}\n|Slovar slovenskega knji\u017enega jezika, Second edition, 2014\n|The official dictionary of modern Slovene is Slovar slovenskega knji\u017enega jezika (SSKJ; Standard Slovene Dictionary). It was published in five volumes by Dr\u017eavna Zalo\u017eba Slovenije between 1970 and 1991 and contains more than 100,000 entries and subentries with accentuation, part-of-speech labels, common collocations, and various qualifiers. In the 1990s, an electronic version of the dictionary was published and it is available online.<ref>http://www.mladinska.com/sskj/o_drugi_izdaji_sskj</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[Finnish language|Finnish]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 102,174 ||0.0001}}\n|[[The New Dictionary of Modern Finnish|Kielitoimiston sanakirja]], 2018\n|Online dictionary. [[Institute for the Languages of Finland]] (governmental institute) has selected the core vocabulary, and many headwords are not included.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.kielitoimistonsanakirja.fi/ | title=Kielitoimiston sanakirja. | publisher=[[Institute for the Languages of Finland]] | accessdate=2019-08-08 | language=Finnish}}</ref>\n\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Polish language|Polish]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 100,000 ||0.0001}}\n|S\u0142ownik j\u0119zyka polskiego PWN \n|Polish dictionary of PWN contains about 100,000 articles and 145,000 definitions.<ref>[https://sjp.pwn.pl]</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[French language|French]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 100,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Dictionnaire Le Grand Robert de la langue fran\u00e7aise]], 2019\n|Contains 100,000 words and 350,000 definitions.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.lerobert.com/dictionnaires/francais/langue/dictionnaire-le-grand-robert-de-la-langue-francaise-abonnement-en-ligne-9782849026069.html | title=Dictionnaire Le Grand Robert de la langue fran\u00e7aise | publisher=[[Edition Le Robert]] | accessdate=5 August 2019|language=French}}</ref>\n\n|-style=\"background:lightgreen\"\n|[[Spanish language|Spanish]]\n|align=right|{{bartable| 93,000 ||0.0001}}\n|[[Diccionario de la lengua espa\u00f1ola de la Real Academia Espa\u00f1ola]], 23rd edition, 2014\n|<ref>{{cite web|title=Presentaci\u00f3n|url=http://www.rae.es/diccionario-de-la-lengua-espanola/presentacion|publisher=[[Real Academia Espa\u00f1ola]]|accessdate=6 August 2016|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n|-\n|[[Dutch languag